---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Teaching That Sticks"
  bodyClass="about-page"
  currentNav="about"
  brandRole="About"
  brandRoleClass="brand-role--lavender"
>

  <!-- ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-inner">
      <div class="about-hero-text">
        <p class="about-kicker">Why this exists</p>
        <h1 class="about-headline">Good teaching doesn't happen by accident — it's designed.</h1>
        <p class="about-hero-sub">
          Teaching That Sticks is a free, openly licensed CPD programme
          for anyone in healthcare who has ever been asked to teach something.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-hero-fox" aria-hidden="true">
        <img
          id="about-fox"
          src="/images/fox/architect.png"
          alt=""
          style="opacity:0;"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Main content ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="about-body">

    <!-- 1. The Problem (fox-left: death_by_powerpoint) -->
    <section class="about-section about-section--fox-left">
      <div class="about-section-fox" aria-hidden="true">
        <!-- swap to death_by_powerpoint.png once copied into public/images/fox/ -->
        <img src="/images/fox/death_by_powerpoint.png" alt="" class="about-fox-img about-fox-img--dbp" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-section-body">
        <p class="about-section-kicker">The problem</p>
        <h2 class="about-section-heading">We keep doing education wrong.</h2>
        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            Someone asks you to &ldquo;do a teaching session&rdquo;. You open PowerPoint.
            You add bullet points until it looks comprehensive. You present it.
            People are polite. Nothing changes.
          </p>
          <p>
            This isn&rsquo;t a failure of effort or expertise. It&rsquo;s a failure of
            <em>default</em> &mdash; a default so embedded in how healthcare
            organisations think about education that it rarely gets questioned.
          </p>
          <ul class="about-problem-list">
            <li>
              <strong>Day-and-done.</strong> Mandatory training delivered once,
              ticked off a spreadsheet, forgotten by Friday. A single passive
              exposure to information does not produce behaviour change.
              We know this. We keep doing it.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Telling people things.</strong> If people just
              <em>knew</em> the right information, they&rsquo;d do the right thing.
              So the solution to every knowledge gap is more slides, more
              pages of policy, more emails to inboxes no-one opens.
              The gap between work as prescribed and work as done widens.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Good education happens by accident.</strong> The debrief
              that ran over. The registrar who ditched slides because the
              projector was broken and found it worked better. These aren&rsquo;t
              flukes. They&rsquo;re glimpses of what education looks like when the
              default gets disrupted.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. Our Solution (fox-right: lightbulb_on) -->
    <section class="about-section about-section--fox-right">
      <div class="about-section-body">
        <p class="about-section-kicker">Our solution</p>
        <h2 class="about-section-heading">Three sessions. The right three.</h2>
        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            We could have built ten sessions. There&rsquo;s easily enough material.
            But we started with a different question: what are the things that,
            if every clinical educator in the country understood them, would
            move the needle most?
          </p>
          <p>
            The answer was surprisingly consistent. How you design information.
            How people actually learn and retain it. How to build sessions that
            change behaviour rather than just deliver content. That&rsquo;s the
            baseline &mdash; and getting that baseline established across the
            workforce was always the priority.
          </p>
          <p>
            Advanced sessions may follow. But these aren&rsquo;t advanced topics for
            formal educators: they&rsquo;re fundamentals that apply whether you&rsquo;re
            running a training day or explaining a procedure to a student on
            shift. The foundation comes first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section-fox" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src="/images/fox/pointing_left.png" alt="" class="about-fox-img" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Beyond the Programme (fox-left: architect) -->
    <section class="about-section about-section--fox-left">
      <div class="about-section-fox" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src="/images/fox/eureka.png" alt="" class="about-fox-img" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-section-body">
        <p class="about-section-kicker">Beyond the programme</p>
        <h2 class="about-section-heading">The knock-on effects.</h2>
        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            The principles here don&rsquo;t stop at the seminar room door.
            A ward email that buries the key information in paragraph four.
            A handover that lists facts without flagging the ones that matter.
            A policy document no-one reads. These are all teaching moments &mdash;
            and they fail for the same reasons bad sessions fail: cognitive
            overload, no retrieval cue, no relevance.
          </p>
          <p>
            One educator who changes their default doesn&rsquo;t just run better
            sessions. They communicate differently. Their learners develop
            higher expectations of teaching. Some of those learners become
            educators. The default starts to shift.
          </p>
          <p>
            Good education is also an equity issue. Dense slides disadvantage
            people with dyslexia. Jargon-heavy delivery disadvantages
            non-native speakers. Designing education well isn&rsquo;t a nicety &mdash;
            it&rsquo;s part of the same professional obligation that governs
            everything else.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Testimonials (full-width, no fox) -->
    <!-- <section class="about-section about-testimonials">
      <p class="about-section-kicker">What people say</p>
      <h2 class="about-section-heading">From people who&rsquo;ve been through it.</h2>
      <div class="about-testimonial-grid">
        <blockquote class="about-testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been teaching for eight years and this was the first time
          anyone had explained <em>why</em> some sessions work and
          others don&rsquo;t.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Senior Registrar, Emergency Medicine</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="about-testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;I came in sceptical &mdash; I&rsquo;ve done a lot of &lsquo;train the trainer&rsquo;
          days. This was genuinely different.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Ward Sister, General Surgery</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="about-testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;The slide session alone changed how I build every presentation
          I give, inside and outside work.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Foundation Year 2 Doctor</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="about-testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;It helped me articulate something I&rsquo;d felt for years but
          couldn&rsquo;t name. Now I can have that conversation with my colleagues.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Clinical Educator, Community Nursing</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <p class="about-testimonial-note">
        Placeholder quotes &mdash; replace with real ones when collected.
      </p>
    </section> -->

    <!-- 5. About the Author (fox-right: thinking) -->
    <section class="about-section about-section--fox-right">
      <div class="about-section-body">
        <p class="about-section-kicker">About the author</p>
        <h2 class="about-section-heading">Who made this?</h2>
        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            I started out as a paramedic. You learn to teach fast in that
            world &mdash; not in seminar rooms, but on the back of an ambulance
            at 3am with a student who needs to be able to do this for real,
            soon. Nobody gave me a framework for that. I picked it up through
            repetition, instinct, and occasionally getting it wrong.
          </p>
          <p>
            I moved into Advanced Practice, eventually into a Trust Lead for
            Enhanced and Advanced Practice, and along the way became a
            University Lecturer &mdash; rebuilding several modules from scratch.
            One was non-medical prescribing: NMC-regulated, taken by
            clinicians with wildly different backgrounds and a patient safety
            endpoint. These weren&rsquo;t sessions where it was fine if people
            forgot by Friday.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most of what&rsquo;s in this programme came from that problem &mdash; designing
            education that <em>had</em> to work. I&rsquo;m a Fellow of the Higher
            Education Academy (FHEA) through AdvanceHE. This is my attempt to
            close the gap between what we know works and what actually gets
            used. Freely, and for anyone who wants it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-section-fox" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src="/images/fox/waving.png" alt="" class="about-fox-img" />
      </div>
    </section>

  </div><!-- /about-body -->

  <!-- ── Ko-fi (full-width tinted) ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="about-kofi">
    <div class="about-kofi-inner">
      <img src="/images/fox/coffee.png" alt="" class="about-kofi-fox" aria-hidden="true" />
      <h2 class="about-kofi-heading">This is free. Help keep it that way.</h2>
      <p class="about-kofi-body">
        Teaching That Sticks is and will remain free. All materials are openly
        licensed. No courses to sell, no subscriptions, no certification fees.
        If you&rsquo;ve found it useful and want to support future sessions and
        maintained materials, a contribution via Ko-fi helps.
      </p>
      <div class="about-kofi-btns">
        <a class="about-kofi-btn about-kofi-btn--cc" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CC&nbsp;BY&nbsp;4.0</a>
        <a class="about-kofi-btn" href="https://ko-fi.com/transilluminate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Support on Ko-fi &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <p class="about-kofi-nudge">No pressure. Genuinely.</p>
    </div>
  </section>



  <fragment slot="styles">
    <style>
      /* ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-hero {
        background: var(--base);
        padding: 4rem 2.5rem 3.5rem;
      }
      .about-hero-inner {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 2.5rem;
      }
      .about-hero-text { flex: 1; }
      .about-hero-fox  { flex-shrink: 0; }
      .about-hero-fox img { width: 180px; }

      .about-kicker,
      .about-section-kicker {
        font-size: 0.6rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--lavender);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }
      .about-headline {
        font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.5vw, 2.4rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.3;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }
      .about-hero-sub {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--subtext0);
        line-height: 1.7;
        max-width: 52ch;
      }

      /* ── Body wrapper ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-body {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 2.5rem 2rem;
      }

      /* ── Sections ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-section {
        padding: 3.5rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--surface0);
      }
      .about-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

      .about-section--fox-left,
      .about-section--fox-right {
        display: grid;
        gap: 3rem;
        align-items: center;
      }
      .about-section--fox-left {
        grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
        grid-template-areas: "fox body";
      }
      .about-section--fox-right {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 180px;
        grid-template-areas: "body fox";
      }
      .about-section-fox  { grid-area: fox;  display: flex; justify-content: center; }
      .about-section-body { grid-area: body; }

      .about-section-heading {
        font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }

      /* ── Fox images ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-fox-img {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 150px;
        max-height: 150px;
        object-fit: contain;
      }
      /* death_by_powerpoint is naturally wider — give it a bit more room */
      .about-fox-img--dbp {
        max-width: 190px;
        max-height: 190px;
      }

      /* ── Prose ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-prose p {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--subtext1);
        line-height: 1.8;
        max-width: 68ch;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      .about-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
      .about-prose a {
        color: var(--peach);
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 2px;
      }
      .about-link-arrow {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.3rem;
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--lavender);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1.5px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--lavender) 40%, transparent);
        padding-bottom: 1px;
        transition: border-color 0.15s;
      }
      .about-link-arrow:hover { border-color: var(--lavender); }

      /* ── Problem list ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-problem-list {
        margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
        padding-left: 0;
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.9rem;
      }
      .about-problem-list li {
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        color: var(--subtext1);
        line-height: 1.75;
        padding-left: 1.1rem;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--surface0);
      }
      .about-problem-list li strong { color: var(--text); }

      /* ── Testimonials ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-testimonial-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
      }
      .about-testimonial {
        background: var(--mantle);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--lavender);
        border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
        padding: 1.25rem 1.25rem 1rem;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .about-testimonial p {
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      }
      .about-testimonial cite {
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--overlay0);
      }
      .about-testimonial-note {
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--overlay0);
        font-style: italic;
      }

      /* ── Ko-fi ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      .about-kofi {
        background: var(--mantle);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--surface0);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--surface0);
        padding: 4rem 2.5rem;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .about-kofi-inner {
        max-width: 480px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .about-kofi-fox {
        width: 110px;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }
      .about-kofi-heading {
        font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      .about-kofi-body {
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        color: var(--subtext1);
        line-height: 1.75;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      }
      .about-kofi-btns {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }
      .about-kofi-btn {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.35rem;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text);
        padding: 0.55rem 1.2rem;
        border: 1.5px solid var(--overlay0);
        border-radius: 6px;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
      }
      .about-kofi-btn:hover { background: var(--surface0); border-color: var(--subtext1); }
      .about-kofi-btn--cc { color: var(--subtext0); border-color: var(--surface0); }
      .about-kofi-btn--cc:hover { color: var(--text); }
      .about-kofi-nudge {
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--overlay0);
        margin-top: 0.75rem;
      }

      /* ── Responsive ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
      @media (max-width: 760px) {
        .about-hero-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
        .about-hero-fox   { display: none; }
        .about-section--fox-left,
        .about-section--fox-right { display: block; }
        .about-section-fox        { display: none; }
        .about-testimonial-grid   { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }
    </style>
  </fragment>

  <fragment slot="scripts">
    <script>
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
        var fox = document.getElementById('about-fox');
        if (fox && (window as any).anime) {
          (window as any).anime({
            targets: fox,
            opacity:    [0, 1],
            translateX: [30, 0],
            duration:   800,
            delay:      250,
            easing:     'easeOutCubic',
          });
        }

        // Animate section fox images as they scroll into view
        var sectionFoxes = document.querySelectorAll('.about-fox-img');
        if (sectionFoxes.length && (window as any).anime) {
          var foxObs = new IntersectionObserver(function(entries) {
            entries.forEach(function(e) {
              if (!e.isIntersecting) return;
              (window as any).anime({
                targets:    e.target,
                opacity:    [0, 1],
                translateY: [16, 0],
                duration:   600,
                easing:     'easeOutCubic',
              });
              foxObs.unobserve(e.target);
            });
          }, { threshold: 0.25 });
          sectionFoxes.forEach(function(img) { foxObs.observe(img); });
        }
      });
    </script>
  </fragment>

</Base>
